{
  "stem": "17135.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 251.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If you behave and you are disciplined and you follow the orders that you get and you work honestly and with effort, you will be treated nicely.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You will get food.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You will be-- if you are sick, we will take care of you.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Just discipline and obedience-- that's all we ask from you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We said to ourselves, oh, my God.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We heard so many terrible things about concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because this was only '39.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I want you to know that tens of thousands, if not hundreds of thousands, of Germans were sent to concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "All those that opposed the Nazis-- communists, socialists, Social Democrats, Jehovah Witnesses, homosexuals.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And-- and when they came back-- some of them were released after a year or two.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were, so to speak, went through a process of re-education.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The Nazis wanted to teach them how good it is to be a German citizen of the Third Reich and they were all wrong, and those that accepted that were released.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they were afraid to tell what is going on, but somehow it filtered through, and we knew that terrible things happened in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then in 1938, after the Kristallnacht, the German Jews-- over 25,000-- were sent to concentration at Dachau, Sachsenhausen, Buchenwald, and they came back and they told what was going on.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were scared to death.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And here is this untersturmfuhrer tells us, if you obey the laws and you work and you are disciplined, nothing will happen to you.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So-- I mean, we were afraid to talk to each other because we didn't-- we were not allowed to talk, but still we whispered.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Maybe it's all propaganda.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Maybe-- maybe we can live through the war here.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because nobody expected the war to last six years.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
